text: The National Museum of Australia is a social history museum in Australia's capital city, Canberra, Australian Capital Territory. It includes displays on the people of Australia, including the Indigenous Australians, the history of settlement and the environment. It was opened in 2001. ==References== ==Other websites== * National Museum of Australia website Category:National museums Category:Museums in Australia Category:Government agencies of Australia Category:Buildings and structures in Canberra Category:2001 establishments in Australia
